{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:07:27.257Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing the Premium Layout**\n\nI'm captivated by the premium feel of the design. The sophisticated layout, notifications, and components are a real standout. Now I'm shifting focus to `/portal/governance` to understand the underlying components and design strategy at work there.\n\n\n**Planning the `/portal/governance`**\n\nI'm deep in the specifics of crafting the `/portal/governance` workspace. The task details are clear: frontend-only, premium feel, and no legal guarantees. I'm focusing on the core components: overview, policy items, human oversight, AI checks, and document governance, each with project, agent, status, and severity filters. Right now, I'm sketching out the design plan in `app/portal/governance/page.tsx`, following the short internal design rules for narrative, metaphor, layout, interaction, mobile, and files.\n\n\n**Defining the Governance Workspace**\n\nI'm now outlining the internal design plan. The narrative establishes this as a command center for real-time compliance oversight, a workspace for inspecting policies, tracking automated checks, managing human oversight, and reviewing logs. The visual metaphor will use a \"Handshake and Seal\" security flow with a HUD-like layout, featuring a dark theme and neon accents. I'm focusing on defining the workspace's look and feel, and am now moving to define the specific layout and components.\n\n\n**Designing the System Diagram**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the architectural graphic. I'm aiming for a clean, CSS/SVG interactive diagram to showcase policy rules and human validation. This will demonstrate how they govern AI agent actions within the enclave. I'm focusing on making it a compelling, visual representation.\n\n**Crafting the Workspace Layout**\n\nI'm refining the layout strategy. The enterprise-grade three-section column/bento layout is taking shape: a header with a governance disclaimer, a top row for key metrics and the interactive SVG, and a unified control panel with interactive filters and a tabbed workspace. I'm considering specific filter options like Project, Agent, Status, and Severity to enhance user control and navigation within the platform.\n\n\n**Refining the Control Panel**\n\nI'm now implementing the three tabs for the control panel, focusing on compliance status, human oversight, and document governance. Tab one will feature compliance standards. Tab two will focus on pending or approved Human-in-the-Loop approvals with direct actions to Approve/Reject. Finally, the third tab, will have cryptographically sealed compliance reports with actions. I'm prioritizing the React filter logic to ensure quick updates in the user interface. I'm focusing on the implementation details now.\n\n\n"}}
