{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:07:53.306Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the Solution**\n\nI've determined that the `DataTable` component is an excellent fit, handling pagination, search, custom actions, and more with grace and security. It is a perfect component that matches the requirements. Now, I will start by designing the solution and incorporating the data.\n\n\n**Organizing the Dashboard**\n\nI'm now structuring `/portal/governance/page.tsx` as a comprehensive dashboard. I'll include a clear disclaimer banner, emphasizing cryptographic sandboxing and no legal guarantees. Following that, I'm designing a page header with a title and a description, as well as a \"TRUST\" badge. Then, a custom filter block will enable granular filtering by Project, Agent, Status, and Severity.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Workflow**\n\nI'm now focusing on the dashboard's visual elements. Specifically, I'm developing a clear, custom SVG to map out the workflow. It will visually depict user input flowing through a prompt interceptor, hardware enclave, human-in-the-loop gateway, and decoupled execution. This graphic will be interactive, allowing users to toggle details and see real-time states by hovering and clicking. In addition, I will create three stat cards to show at-a-glance key metrics, such as Active Guardrails and Pending Human Oversights.\n\n\n**Unifying the Interface**\n\nI'm now integrating AI operations checks, policy rules, and human oversight into a unified system. I'm leaning toward a tabbed interface for workspace modules, with tabs for guardrails/AI checks, human oversight actions, and secure document governance. These tabs will filter by project, agent, and severity and incorporate interactive elements.\n\n\n**Defining Mock Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on defining mock datasets to feed the page filters and tables. To achieve ultra-responsive interactions, I plan to manage all the data within React state. I've outlined project, agent, status, and severity options, ensuring they're dynamic or explicit. Also, I'm now looking at the existing mock data model to integrate it deeply and seamlessly.\n\n\n**Structuring the Policies**\n\nI am now enriching the policy and governance items. I'm adding `project`, `agent`, `status`, and `severity` fields to the existing data structure to enable dynamic and efficient filtering capabilities. I'm focusing on defining clear and comprehensive policy items and AI checks, which will include detailed information about each rule, such as rule IDs, names, standards, statuses, and descriptions. For instance, I'm documenting ISO-27001 cryptographic key hygiene and SOC2 sandboxed host execution rules with all the information required. This will be the foundation for user interaction.\n\n\n**Expanding the Policies**\n\nI'm now detailing policy items. I am introducing additional policy rules, specifically focusing on \"Sovereign Compliance Model Audit Range,\" \"Patient Identity Isolation Enclave,\" and \"GDPR Decoupled Data Residency Validator\". For each item, I've outlined their Rule IDs, names, standards, statuses, severity levels, associated projects and agents, and descriptions. These policy rule details are essential for dynamic filtering and user understanding.\n\n\n**Defining Oversight Points**\n\nI'm now outlining key human oversight points to integrate into the interface. I've focused on pending approval items, ensuring their inclusion for user action. I will now integrate them into the existing data structure to enable dynamic and efficient filtering capabilities. I've been thinking, and now I'm working on defining rule data, such as `GOV-EXEC-F`, `GOV-SAND-G`, and adding a new rule for localized thread boundary locks.\n\n\n**Integrating Oversight Actions**\n\nI'm now integrating the human oversight points. I've created interactive panels for each, offering \"Approve\" and \"Reject\" actions. I've designed these to fit seamlessly within the \"Human Oversight Points\" requirement, ensuring dynamic interaction from Alexander Mercer or current client roles. I've detailed examples of oversight items.\n\n\n**Defining Document Governance**\n\nI'm now expanding oversight to include document governance. I've defined a structure for compliance-related files, listing details like document ID, name, size, format, project, agent, status, and severity. I am now working on a second document governance item as an example. I want to ensure this data integrates seamlessly with the existing interface.\n\n\n\n**Expanding Document Governance**\n\nI'm now integrating more document governance data. I'm incorporating detailed document metadata, including file sizes, formats, upload timestamps, categories, clearance levels, and security hashes, to ensure comprehensive file tracking. I'm focusing on seamless integration, for instance, a YAML file for SOC2 compliance with the hash `0x3FBC128EE809FF9CC9810A88AA11B8FFFA02CE8274A08B0192A45C89FBC10492` and also a NIST AI RMF telemetry report with the hash `0xDE897FF021BC8102C019FFAD998E1256E3B890CC7FFADE138EE87A02FF90A11B`.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Topology**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing the SVG architecture diagram, determined to craft a visually compelling and interactive representation of the workflow. I've successfully mapped the topology to five nodes, each representing a key stage: Request Input, Guardrail Attestation, Isolated Hardware, Human Interlock, and Compliant Execution. Clicking a node now triggers detailed telemetry display or state changes, bringing the process to life. I have completed the basic structure, and now I'm working on the design.\n\n\n**Refining the Visuals**\n\nI'm now implementing the interface's visual aspects based on our specifications. I'm focusing on a dark, premium aesthetic with deep black backgrounds, muted text, sharp borders, and glow effects, avoiding color overload. I'm leveraging `lucide-react` icons consistently, checking the icon usage in other files to ensure uniformity. I'm also preparing for hover micro-interactions on the SVG architecture diagram, the Bento grid, and interactive elements.\n\n\n"}}
