ing unique project and agent values directly from the `policies`, `approvals`, and `documents` data. I'm dynamically generating project and agent lists for dropdowns. This eliminates hardcoded values and makes the filtering interactive. My next step involves integrating these lists into the filter component.\n\n\n**Designing Notification Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating a notification toaster system into the component. Whenever a user approves, rejects, or re-verifies, I will trigger a temporary status notification at the top/bottom of the page or inside the layout. I'm adding a custom notification/toast state, a standard feature for a premium UI. I'm designing the custom SVG interaction.\n\n\n**Visualizing Workflow Steps**\n\nI'm now visualizing the operational workflow as a real-time data inspection pipeline, and designing steps for a dynamic, interactive SVG diagram. I'm focusing on defining steps in the workflow, including 'Prompt Ingress Node,' 'Guardrail Interception Gate,' 'Hardware Security Enclave,' and 'Human Oversight Interlock.' Each will include details like title, status, metric, and a description.\n\n\n**Designing Flow Rail**\n\nI'm now designing the visual representation of the workflow. I'm focusing on a modern, cyber-themed horizontal flow rail with connected steps. Each step will have a glowing dot with an appropriate icon, and an animated SVG line indicating data flow. Clicking a step sets an `activeDiagramStep` state, displaying detailed information below.\n\n\n**Revising Bento Grid Layout**\n\nI'm revisiting the Bento grid layout. I've decided on a responsive `grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6`. The first two columns (lg:col-span-2) will feature the \"Enclave Interceptor & Guardrail Topology\" diagram due to its visual impact. The third column (lg:col-span-1) will contain the \"Oversight Overview & Metrics Panel\" with three metric-style boxes. This structure will provide a comprehensive overview and highlight key metrics.\n\nI've also re-confirmed the filters: Project, Agent, Status, Severity, and Search. I'm now picturing a premium horizontal filter bar with a search input and four styled select dropdowns. I will integrate a \"Reset Filters\" button.\n\n\n**Styling Filter Elements**\n\nI'm now styling the filter selectors with custom borders, a glowing focus state, and a subtle monospace font. I'm focusing on the visual hierarchy and feel of the user interface.\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm structuring the content tabs: The first tab is for **AI Guardrails & Policies**, with a styled policy list and detailed policy information displayed upon click, including cryptographic ledger logs and a \"Verify Guardrail\" button with visual feedback. The second tab, **Human Oversight Interlocks**, presents a list of approval requests with key details and visual cues for severity.\n\n\n**Implementing Approval Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the approval logic within the workflow. I'm focusing on the visual cues for approved and rejected items, specifically the \"Approve Handshake\" and \"Decline Handshake\" buttons. These will trigger status updates, log events, and generate toasts, including trust index adjustments for successful approvals. I am now coding these.\n\n\n**Verifying Import Consistency**\n\nI'm now making final checks on import statements to ensure code cleanliness and compile safety. I'm verifying the current content of `app/portal/governance/page.tsx` for possible replacement. I am going back over the imports of `previewProjects`, `previewAgentOperations`, and `previewGovernanceItems` to ensure there are no collisions or naming conflicts.\n\n\n**Refining Default State**\n\nI'm solidifying the default React state to encompass all data with added metadata for robust filtering. I'm focusing on incorporating project ID, agent ID, status, and severity across all items, ensuring a comprehensive dataset for dynamic filtering. This enriched state will guarantee precise control and reliable filter functionality.\n\n\n"}}
