{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:10:51.346Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Animation Compatibility**\n\nI've realized that the animations in `lib/animations.ts` are quite standard. The good news is that this opens the door to using standard Tailwind classes for CSS transitions, like `transition-all duration-300`, plus styling the flow lines with CSS animations. The advantage is great compatibility!\n\n\n**Verifying Animation Safety**\n\nI'm now focusing on ensuring the flow line animations are bulletproof. I've considered and prototyped using standard CSS keyframes directly within the component using `<style>` tags. I realized that a more robust approach is to use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`, avoiding any dependencies on external libraries and ensuring broader compatibility across environments. This inline approach provides a simple, maintainable, and portable animation solution.\n\n\n**Designing SVG Node Structure**\n\nI'm now diving into the SVG's structural design. I plan to create a full-width SVG on desktop with five evenly spaced nodes and connecting lines, animated with `animate-flow-line`. Each node will be a visually rich `circle` or `rect` containing an icon or text. I'm exploring the best way to render the nodes, either as native SVG shapes or positioned HTML elements, possibly flexed along a row or on an absolute grid to ensure responsive layout.\n\n\n**Optimizing the Node Layout**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on a fully responsive and accessible layout. I'm exploring a flexbox approach with five \"step\" cards in a row on desktop and a column on mobile. This elegantly adapts to various screen sizes without hardcoded positioning. These steps will be clickable cards with a large circular badge containing an icon, like a glowing cyan border if compliant or amber if a warning, and connecting arrows. The mobile version uses down arrows, while desktop employs right arrows.\n\n\n**Implementing the Node Details**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in the design details of the nodes. I've decided on integrating icons like `ShieldCheck`, `Lock`, and `UserCheck`. Below the circles, each step will feature a title, and a status indicator. On hover or activation, a subtle cyan or blue glow shadow effect will highlight the step. Clicking a step will display its full technical details in an adjacent detail box.\n\nI'm also working on a disclaimer banner: \"Designed to support governance workflows, no guarantees.\" I will write a disclaimer block at the top of the page, formatted as an official, sealed trust notice: bordered with `#009DFF` with a Lock icon, with the text: \"This Sovereign Governance Workspace is designed to support client-managed compliance and auditing workflows. GFF AI provides real-time mathematical validation, sandboxed boundaries, and policy ledger check capabilities. All metrics, compliance ratings, and automated policies are simulated sandbox boundaries designed to support governance workflows and do not constitute formal legal, regulatory, or compliance guarantees.\"\n\n\n**Defining Filter Controls**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the filter panel. I've defined states for project, agent, status, severity, and search term. I'm generating dropdown options based on the available data, including projects like \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02,\" agents like \"RETAIL-CORE-A1,\" and statuses such as \"compliant\" and \"warning.\" The goal is to build a responsive and user-friendly interface for managing data.\n\n\n**Refining Filter Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the filtering logic for the control panel, adding \"non_compliant\" and \"critical\" as valid options for status and severity filters, and integrating these into the existing filter states. I'm focusing on ensuring that the filter checks work correctly, checking if a filter is set and if it matches. I've also implemented an empty state for cases where the filters eliminate all results, to display \"No active guardrail policies match your filter.\"\n\n\n**Evaluating Interface Choices**\n\nI'm now reconsidering the data display strategy, realizing that a custom tabbed interface would offer significantly more premium and interactive control compared to a simple table. This would enable granular actions like policy expansion, approval/decline options, and hash copying. I am focusing on this new approach and will be working on it. I also decided we will run lint and build to make sure things are clean and ready to go.\n\n\n**Designing the New Interface**\n\nI'm now writing the governance page at `/app/portal/governance/page.tsx`. Instead of using a basic table, I'm integrating a custom data table, while ensuring the components from `@/components/private-app`, such as `WorkspaceCard` and `StatusBadge`, are imported for integration. I've drafted the page structure, and I'm importing all necessary `lucide-react` icons. I am very excited by the potential!\n\n\n**Implementing Toast Notifications**\n\nI'm now implementing toast notifications for user feedback. I'm focusing on a bottom-right container, utilizing Tailwind classes for styling and animations. I've designed various toast types—success, warning, and info—each with distinct icons and colors, all using `lucide-react`. The toast container will handle a stack of these notifications, providing clear and concise feedback to the user.\n\n\n\n**Defining Animation Keyframes**\n\nI've decided to define CSS animations inline using `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`. Specifically, I'm working on keyframes for slide-up effects and pulse glows, directly within the component's `<style>` tags. I'm excited that this simple, inline approach provides a completely native, high-end feel for the app. I'm focusing on ensuring these animations are smooth and consistent.\n\n\n\n**Adding Interactive Policy Controls**\n\nI'm now implementing interactive policy controls. I've added a feature to set policy approval status to `\"rejected\"`, along with a toast notification: `\"Oversight request OVS-xxx declined by client.\"`. Also, I'm integrating \"Verify\" buttons, complete with loading spinners and status updates; for example, I'm setting a local loading state for policy ID's. On verification, after 1.2 seconds, the policy status updates to \"compliant\", with a toast: `\"ISO/SOC policy GOV-xxx verified: compliance check successfully logged.\"` I'm thrilled with the high-fidelity interactivity!\n\n\n\n**Calculating the Trust Index**\n\nI'm now calculating the Overall Trust Index dynamically. My approach involves a base of 95%, then deducts percentages based on policy status. Specifically, 5% is deducted for each `critical` or `non_compliant` policy, 2% for each `warning`, and 1% for each `pending` approval. I also add 2% for each `approved` human oversight, up to a maximum of 100%. This dynamic calculation reflects the current state of active policies and pending approvals accurately.\n\n\n**Designing the SVG Diagram**\n\nI'm now fully focused on the design of the SVG interactive diagram, and excited by the potential! I have decided on five distinct nodes representing the processing pipeline: Prompt Ingress, Guardrail Interception, Hardware Security Enclave, Human Oversight Interlock, and Sealed State Ledger. I plan to render these nodes within the SVG with connecting lines and rich visual cues and animations, ensuring they clearly convey the workflow's progression.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Step Details**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive step details section of the SVG diagram. I'm focusing on a right-hand panel that dynamically displays technical specifications based on the `activeStep` state. Each step will have a unique neon color theme: Light Blue for Ingress, Cyan for Guardrail, Violet/Purple for Enclave, Amber/Yellow for Human, and Emerald Green for Ledger. I am aiming to create a highly aesthetic layout for each step within the diagram container. I will render each step as a neon glowing border with a bright color theme.\n\n\n**Refining Neon Node Visuals**\n\nI'm now refining the visual details of the neon nodes within the SVG diagram. I've focused on ensuring the color themes are distinct and appealing. The Light Blue Ingress, Cyan Guardrail, Violet Enclave, Amber Human Oversight, and Emerald Ledger all have unique, glowing neon borders. I'm focusing on their visual appeal, as this will play a key role in the user experience of the interactive flow.\n\n\n\n**Refining Active State Styling**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the active state styling for each node. I've successfully implemented dynamic border colors and background glows based on the `activeStep` state. Each step now features a distinct neon glow: Light Blue, Cyan, Violet, Amber, and Emerald Green. I'm focusing on ensuring these active state styles clearly indicate the currently selected step in the diagram, and am refining the `bgGlow` styles to emphasize the user's progress.\n\n\n**Styling the Neon Node Icons**\n\nI'm working on refining the appearance of the node icons, now using `Cpu`, `ShieldCheck`, `Lock`, `UserCheck`, and `FileText` from `lucide-react`. I'm focusing on their positioning and styling within each node to enhance visual clarity and ensure they match the overall aesthetic of the neon design. I'm also ensuring the icons' size and color contrast with the glow effects.\n\n\n**Refining the Step Details**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive technical detail display for each step in the diagram. I'm focusing on populating the right-hand panel with dynamic information derived from the `activeStep` state. Each step will include detailed specifications, enhancing the user experience. I am enjoying the process, I am almost done!\n\n\n**Finalizing Diagram Display**\n\nI'm now putting the finishing touches on the interactive diagram and am very excited with the result! I've confirmed that hovering or clicking steps allows clients to explore the architecture in real-time, with a side panel displaying live metrics and descriptions. This fully satisfies all project requirements: the custom SVG/CSS architecture graphic, narrative timeline, operating model diagram, hover micro-interactions, and the premium custom strategic feel. I'm very happy with how it turned out.\n\n\n\n**Confirming Client Portal Structure**\n\nI've confirmed I don't need to write any code for sidebars or navigation since the `ClientPortalLayout` handles those elements automatically. My focus will be on the interior content of the governance page. I am so glad, this simplifies the code I must write!\n\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:10:51.377Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"hjegmaa8","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/portal/governance/page.tsx","old_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React from \"react\";\nimport { DataTable, previewGovernanceItems, TableColumn, GovernanceItem } from \"@/components/private-app\";\n\nexport default function ClientGovernancePage() {\n  const columns: TableColumn<GovernanceItem>[] = [\n    { key: \"id\", header: \"Rule ID\", sortable: true },\n    { key: \"name\", header: \"Policy Guardrail Name\", sortable: true },\n    { key: \"standard\", header: \"Compliance standard\", sortable: true },\n    { key: \"lastChecked\", header: \"Last Verified\" },\n    { key: \"status\", header: \"Audit State\", sortable: true }\n  ];\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n      <div>\n        <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight font-mono uppercase\">Guardrail Policies</h2>\n        <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 mt-1\">Active guardrail rulebooks, sandbox boundaries, and regulatory policy compliance parameters.</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <DataTable \n        columns={columns}\n        data={previewGovernanceItems}\n        pageSize={5}\n        searchPlaceholder=\"Search guardrails by standards or name...\"\n        searchKeys={[\"id\", \"name\", \"standard\", \"status\"]}\n        statusField=\"status\"\n        typeField=\"standard\"\n        categoryLabel=\"GOVERNANCE POLICY\"\n        detailTitle={(row) => row.name}\n        renderDetail={(row) => (\n          <div className=\"space-y-5 font-mono text-[11.5px]\">\n            <div className=\"p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/40 space-y-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-white/30 text-[9px] uppercase font-bold\">Policy Summary</span>\n              <p className=\"text-white font-bold text-[13px]\">{row.name}</p>\n            </div>\n            \n            <div className=\"p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/40 space-y-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-white/30 text-[9px] uppercase font-bold\">Enforcement Boundary</span>\n              <p className=\"text-white/75 leading-relaxed\">{row.desc}</p>\n            </div>\n\n            <div className=\"p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/40 space-y-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-white/30 text-[9px] uppercase font-bold\">Audit Ledger Details</span>\n              <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-[10.5px]\">\n                <div className=\"flex justify-between\"><span className=\"text-white/40\">Standard:</span><span className=\"text-white font-bold\">{row.standard}</span></div>\n                <div className=\"flex justify-between\"><span className=\"text-white/40\">State:</span><span className=\"text-[#00FFC2] font-bold\">{row.status.toUpperCase()}</span></div>\n                <div className=\"flex justify-between col-span-2 pt-1 border-t border-white/5\"><span className=\"text-white/40\">Last Verified:</span><span className=\"text-white/60\">{new Date(row.lastChecked).toLocaleString()}</span></div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        )}\n      />\n    </div>\n  );\n}","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { \n  ShieldCheck, \n  ShieldAlert, \n  CheckCircle, \n  AlertCircle, \n  Clock, \n  FileText, \n  Copy, \n  Check, \n  Search, \n  X, \n  ChevronRight, \n  ChevronDown, \n  Download, \n  Lock, \n  RefreshCw, \n  UserCheck, \n  ThumbsUp, \n  ThumbsDown,\n  Info,\n  Layers,\n  Cpu,\n  SlidersHorizontal,\n  ExternalLink,\n  RotateCcw\n} from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { WorkspaceCard, StatusBadge } from \"@/components/private-app\";\n\n// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// 1. DATA DEFINITIONS (FILTERABLE & INTERACTIVE MOCK SCHEMAS)\n// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ninterface PolicyItem {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  standard: \"ISO-27001\" | \"SOC2 Type II\" | \"HIPAA\" | \"GDPR Enclave\" | \"NIST AI RMF\";\n  status: \"compliant\" | \"warning\" | \"critical\";\n  severity: \"high\" | \"medium\" | \"low\";\n  projectId: string;\n  projectName: string;\n  agentId: string;\n  agentName: string;\n  desc: string;\n  lastChecked: string;\n  logs: string[];\n}\n\ninterface HumanOversightItem {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  project: string;\n  projectId: string;\n  agent: string;\n  agentId: string;\n  requester: string;\n  status: \"pending\" | \"approved\" | \"rejected\";\n  severity: \"high\" | \"medium\" | \"low\";\n  requestDate: string;\n  category: \"Access Elevation\" | \"Model Boundary Shift\" | \"HSM Seal Rollover\";\n  desc: string;\n}\n\ninterface DocumentItem {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  size: string;\n  format: \"PDF\" | \"YAML\" | \"CSV\";\n  projectId: string;\n  projectName: string;\n  agentId: string;\n  agentName: string;\n  status: \"compliant\" | \"warning\" | \"critical\";\n  severity: \"high\" | \"medium\" | \"low\";\n  hash: string;\n  uploadedAt: string;\n  category: \"audit\" | \"governance\" | \"agreement\";\n  clearanceLevel: string;\n}\n\nexport default function ClientGovernancePage() {\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 2. STATE INITIALIZATION\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  // Base state for policies and automated checks\n  const [policies, setPolicies] = useState<PolicyItem[]>([\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-27001-A\",\n      name: \"ISO-27001 Cryptographic Key Hygiene\",\n      standard: \"ISO-27001\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-001\",\n      agentName: \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\",\n      desc: \"Enforces a 30-day automatic key rotation cycle inside isolated HSM memory pools to maintain secure credential separation.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T11:00:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Initializing key rotation handshake with hardware security module...\",\n        \"Cryptographic root keys verified via zero-knowledge proof.\",\n        \"Rotation completed successfully. Signature: 0x8FDE...AA\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-SOC2-B\",\n      name: \"eBPF Sandboxed Host Execution Boundaries\",\n      standard: \"SOC2 Type II\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-001\",\n      agentName: \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\",\n      desc: \"Active kernel-level monitoring ensuring sandbox containers cannot inspect host system memory space or adjacent thread segments.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T11:30:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Streaming eBPF ring buffer events...\",\n        \"Verifying isolation boundaries: Host syscall table locked.\",\n        \"Zero boundary violations detected during current epoch transaction stream.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-NIST-C\",\n      name: \"Sovereign Compliance Model Audit Range\",\n      standard: \"NIST AI RMF\",\n      status: \"warning\",\n      severity: \"medium\",\n      projectId: \"proj-002\",\n      projectName: \"Model Guardrail Sandbox 04\",\n      agentId: \"agent-002\",\n      agentName: \"ALIGN-GUARD-A2\",\n      desc: \"Requires continuous prompt/response filtering log streams. Alert: Disk allocation on telemetry nodes exceeds warning threshold.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T10:15:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Analyzing prompt embedding distribution...\",\n        \"Detected high-density logs approach warning threshold: 88% capacity reached.\",\n        \"Recommendation: Archive current epoch log stream to secure cold storage.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-HIPAA-D\",\n      name: \"Patient Identity Isolation Enclave\",\n      standard: \"HIPAA\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-004\",\n      agentName: \"MED-CLINIC-H9\",\n      desc: \"Cryptographically redacts high-risk patient fields inside secure enclave boundaries before data transits outside isolated memory.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T09:00:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Intercepted medical inference request payload...\",\n        \"Identified 4 PII entities. Running localized token sanitization...\",\n        \"Payload sanitized. Handed off to Model Execution Unit.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-GDPR-E\",\n      name: \"GDPR Decoupled Data Residency Validator\",\n      standard: \"GDPR Enclave\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      projectId: \"proj-003\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Mining Intel Loop\",\n      agentId: \"agent-003\",\n      agentName: \"ORE-TUNNEL-X4\",\n      desc: \"Ensures all localized inference threads maintain absolute physical data residency locks inside specified EU jurisdictions.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T08:45:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Validating physical host execution coordinates...\",\n        \"Verified latitude/longitude bounds inside approved Schengen zone.\",\n        \"Data residency restriction locked to local hardware storage blocks.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-EXEC-F\",\n      name: \"Thread Allocation Leak-Gate Check\",\n      standard: \"NIST AI RMF\",\n      status: \"critical\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-004\",\n      agentName: \"MED-CLINIC-H9\",\n      desc: \"Monitors context leaks and anomalous CPU utilization. Alert: Thread load exceeds safe operating threshold (94%).\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-27T11:58:11Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Anomaly detector triggered: Thread load sustained at 94.5% for >10m.\",\n        \"Memory leak scan initiated... No active leaks detected.\",\n        \"Recommended action: Manually spin up adjacent Intel SGX scale node.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"GOV-SAND-G\",\n      name: \"Decoupled Hardware State Handshake\",\n      standard: \"SOC2 Type II\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"low\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-005\",\n      agentName: \"TRANS-LOOP-Z1\",\n      desc: \"Verifies continuous heartbeat from decoupled hardware enclaves. Status: Terminated gracefully by operator.\",\n      lastChecked: \"2026-06-26T23:55:00Z\",\n      logs: [\n        \"Heartbeat signal missing from enclave node TRANS-LOOP-Z1.\",\n        \"Checking decoupling audit trail... Graceful exit signature confirmed by user admin.\",\n        \"Status recorded as DECOUPLED. Standard compliance active.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ]);\n\n  // Base state for Human Oversight interlock approvals\n  const [approvals, setApprovals] = useState<HumanOversightItem[]>([\n    {\n      id: \"OVS-001\",\n      title: \"Elevate Alexander Mercer to Level IV Clearance (Temporary)\",\n      project: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      agent: \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\",\n      agentId: \"agent-001\",\n      requester: \"Apex Sovereign Group\",\n      status: \"pending\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      requestDate: \"2026-06-27T11:15:00Z\",\n      category: \"Access Elevation\",\n      desc: \"Requested temporary context elevation to inspect active HSM enclave raw decryption socket for debugging keys.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"OVS-002\",\n      title: \"Shift Model Boundary Execution Parameters\",\n      project: \"Model Guardrail Sandbox 04\",\n      projectId: \"proj-002\",\n      agent: \"ALIGN-GUARD-A2\",\n      agentId: \"agent-002\",\n      requester: \"Alexander Mercer\",\n      status: \"pending\",\n      severity: \"medium\",\n      requestDate: \"2026-06-27T10:45:00Z\",\n      category: \"Model Boundary Shift\",\n      desc: \"Approve shift of semantic boundary threshold from 0.85 to 0.75 to accommodate specialized geological classification queries.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"OVS-003\",\n      title: \"Force HSM Cryptographic Seal Manual Key Rollover\",\n      project: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      agent: \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\",\n      agentId: \"agent-001\",\n      requester: \"Dr. Sarah Vance\",\n      status: \"approved\",\n      severity: \"high\",\n      requestDate: \"2026-06-25T09:00:00Z\",\n      category: \"HSM Seal Rollover\",\n      desc: \"Manually sign and seal physical root security keys to resolve pending key-rotation delays.\"\n    }\n  ]);\n\n  // Base state for Document Governance\n  const [documents, setDocuments] = useState<DocumentItem[]>([\n    {\n      id: \"DOC-GOV-01\",\n      name: \"ISO27001_Sovereign_Sandbox_Audit_2026.pdf\",\n      size: \"4.8 MB\",\n      format: \"PDF\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-001\",\n      agentName: \"RETAIL-CORE-A1\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"medium\",\n      hash: \"0x8FDE3102C130D7B2D26788AB0E8A850CE3207FFCDE10B74E824A45B12A4F23AA\",\n      uploadedAt: \"2026-05-12T10:30:00Z\",\n      category: \"audit\",\n      clearanceLevel: \"LEVEL_III\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"DOC-GOV-02\",\n      name: \"Guardrail_Ruleset_SOC2_Compliance_Signed.yaml\",\n      size: \"24 KB\",\n      format: \"YAML\",\n      projectId: \"proj-002\",\n      projectName: \"Model Guardrail Sandbox 04\",\n      agentId: \"agent-002\",\n      agentName: \"ALIGN-GUARD-A2\",\n      status: \"compliant\",\n      severity: \"low\",\n      hash: \"0x3FBC128EE809FF9CC9810A88AA11B8FFFA02CE8274A08B0192A45C89FBC10492\",\n      uploadedAt: \"2026-06-01T15:45:00Z\",\n      category: \"governance\",\n      clearanceLevel: \"LEVEL_IV\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"DOC-GOV-03\",\n      name: \"NIST_AI_RMF_Alignment_Telemetry_Report.pdf\",\n      size: \"2.4 MB\",\n      format: \"PDF\",\n      projectId: \"proj-001\",\n      projectName: \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\",\n      agentId: \"agent-004\",\n      agentName: \"MED-CLINIC-H9\",\n      status: \"warning\",\n      severity: \"medium\",\n      hash: \"0xDE897FF021BC8102C019FFAD998E1256E3B890CC7FFADE138EE87A02FF90A11B\",\n      uploadedAt: \"2026-06-27T10:20:00Z\",\n      category: \"audit\",\n      clearanceLevel: \"LEVEL_IV\"\n    }\n  ]);\n\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 3. SELECTION & FILTER STATES\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  const [selectedProject, setSelectedProject] = useState(\"\");\n  const [selectedAgent, setSelectedAgent] = useState(\"\");\n  const [selectedStatus, setSelectedStatus] = useState(\"\");\n  const [selectedSeverity, setSelectedSeverity] = useState(\"\");\n  const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState(\"\");\n\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<\"policies\" | \"oversight\" | \"documents\">(\"policies\");\n  const [expandedPolicyId, setExpandedPolicyId] = useState<string | null>(\"GOV-27001-A\");\n  const [activeStep, setActiveStep] = useState(\"step-4\");\n\n  // Interaction temporary states\n  const [verifyingId, setVerifyingId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [exportingId, setExportingId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [toasts, setToasts] = useState<{ id: string; message: string; type: \"success\" | \"info\" | \"warning\" }[]>([]);\n\n  // Toast notifier helper\n  const addToast = (message: string, type: \"success\" | \"info\" | \"warning\" = \"success\") => {\n    const id = Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 9);\n    setToasts(prev => [...prev, { id, message, type }]);\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setToasts(prev => prev.filter(t => t.id !== id));\n    }, 4000);\n  };\n\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 4. DYNAMIC FILTER DERIVATIONS\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  const filteredPolicies = policies.filter(p => {\n    if (selectedProject && p.projectId !== selectedProject) return false;\n    if (selectedAgent && p.agentId !== selectedAgent) return false;\n    if (selectedStatus && p.status !== selectedStatus) return false;\n    if (selectedSeverity && p.severity !== selectedSeverity) return false;\n    if (searchTerm) {\n      const s = searchTerm.toLowerCase();\n      const match = p.name.toLowerCase().includes(s) || \n                    p.desc.toLowerCase().includes(s) || \n                    p.standard.toLowerCase().includes(s) ||\n                    p.id.toLowerCase().includes(s);\n      if (!match) return false;\n    }\n    return true;\n  });\n\n  const filteredApprovals = approvals.filter(a => {\n    if (selectedProject && a.projectId !== selectedProject) return false;\n    if (selectedAgent && a.agentId !== selectedAgent) return false;\n    if (selectedStatus && a.status !== selectedStatus) return false;\n    if (selectedSeverity && a.severity !== selectedSeverity) return false;\n    if (searchTerm) {\n      const s = searchTerm.toLowerCase();\n      const match = a.title.toLowerCase().includes(s) || \n                    a.desc.toLowerCase().includes(s) || \n                    a.category.toLowerCase().includes(s) ||\n                    a.id.toLowerCase().includes(s);\n      if (!match) return false;\n    }\n    return true;\n  });\n\n  const filteredDocuments = documents.filter(d => {\n    if (selectedProject && d.projectId !== selectedProject) return false;\n    if (selectedAgent && d.agentId !== selectedAgent) return false;\n    if (selectedStatus && d.status !== selectedStatus) return false;\n    if (selectedSeverity && d.severity !== selectedSeverity) return false;\n    if (searchTerm) {\n      const s = searchTerm.toLowerCase();\n      const match = d.name.toLowerCase().includes(s) || \n                    d.category.toLowerCase().includes(s) ||\n                    d.id.toLowerCase().includes(s);\n      if (!match) return false;\n    }\n    return true;\n  });\n\n  // Unique options extracted dynamically for filters\n  const projectOptions = Array.from(new Set([\n    ...policies.map(p => JSON.stringify({ id: p.projectId, name: p.projectName })),\n    ...approvals.map(a => JSON.stringify({ id: a.projectId, name: a.project })),\n    ...documents.map(d => JSON.stringify({ id: d.projectId, name: d.projectName }))\n  ])).map(str => JSON.parse(str)) as { id: string; name: string }[];\n\n  const agentOptions = Array.from(new Set([\n    ...policies.map(p => JSON.stringify({ id: p.agentId, name: p.agentName })),\n    ...approvals.map(a => JSON.stringify({ id: a.agentId, name: a.agent })),\n    ...documents.map(d => JSON.stringify({ id: d.agentId, name: d.agentName }))\n  ])).map(str => JSON.parse(str)) as { id: string; name: string }[];\n\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 5. DYNAMIC WORKSPACE METRICS (CALCULATED IN REAL TIME FOR WORKFLOW SUPPORT)\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  const totalPolicies = policies.length;\n  const compliantPolicies = policies.filter(p => p.status === \"compliant\").length;\n  const criticalPolicies = policies.filter(p => p.status === \"critical\").length;\n  const warningPolicies = policies.filter(p => p.status === \"warning\").length;\n  const pendingOversights = approvals.filter(a => a.status === \"pending\").length;\n  const approvedOversights = approvals.filter(a => a.status === \"approved\").length;\n\n  // Real-time calculation of dynamic trust score\n  // Designed to simulate high-fidelity response when client acts on decisions\n  const dynamicTrustScore = Math.min(100, Math.max(0, \n    99 - (criticalPolicies * 8) - (warningPolicies * 3) - (pendingOversights * 1.5) + (approvedOversights * 0.8)\n  )).toFixed(1);\n\n  // Reset all filters helper\n  const handleResetFilters = () => {\n    setSelectedProject(\"\");\n    setSelectedAgent(\"\");\n    setSelectedStatus(\"\");\n    setSelectedSeverity(\"\");\n    setSearchTerm(\"\");\n    addToast(\"All governance filters reset successfully\", \"info\");\n  };\n\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 6. INTERACTIVE ACTION HANDLERS\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n  // Verification simulation for Automated Guardrail Policies\n  const handleVerifyPolicy = (policyId: string) => {\n    if (verifyingId) return;\n    setVerifyingId(policyId);\n    addToast(`Triggered real-time verification handshake for rule ${policyId}...`, \"info\");\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setPolicies(prev => prev.map(p => {\n        if (p.id === policyId) {\n          const timestamp = new Date().toISOString();\n          const updatedLogs = [\n            `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] RE-VERIFY: Context state check initiated.`,\n            `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] HANDSHAKE: Cryptographic proof confirmed by isolated host processor.`,\n            `[${new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}] LOCK SUCCESS: Enforcement boundary verified 100% compliant.`,\n            ...p.logs\n          ].slice(0, 6); // Keep logs trimmed\n\n          return {\n            ...p,\n            status: \"compliant\" as const,\n            lastChecked: timestamp,\n            logs: updatedLogs\n          };\n        }\n        return p;\n      }));\n      setVerifyingId(null);\n      addToast(`Guardrail ${policyId} verified: Enclave parameters are locked and compliant.`, \"success\");\n    }, 1200);\n  };\n\n  // Approval action for human interlocks\n  const handleResolveApproval = (id: string, action: \"approved\" | \"rejected\") => {\n    setApprovals(prev => prev.map(a => {\n      if (a.id === id) {\n        return { ...a, status: action };\n      }\n      return a;\n    }));\n\n    if (action === \"approved\") {\n      addToast(`Human interlock ${id} cryptographically signed & approved.`, \"success\");\n    } else {\n      addToast(`Human interlock ${id} declined. State remains isolated.`, \"warning\");\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Certificate compilation simulation\n  const handleExportDocument = (docId: string) => {\n    if (exportingId) return;\n    setExportingId(docId);\n    addToast(`Compiling cryptographic audit ledger for certificate ${docId}...`, \"info\");\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setExportingId(null);\n      addToast(`Attestation Certificate ${docId} exported and cryptographically sealed.`, \"success\");\n    }, 1500);\n  };\n\n  const handleCopyHash = (hash: string) => {\n    navigator.clipboard.writeText(hash);\n    addToast(\"Cryptographic seal hash copied to clipboard\", \"success\");\n  };\n\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  // 7. INTERACTIVE DIAGRAM DATA\n  // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  const diagramSteps = [\n    {\n      id: \"step-1\",\n      title: \"1. Prompt Ingress Node\",\n      status: \"verified\",\n      metric: \"0.4ms latency\",\n      desc: \"Client-facing model transaction inputs are ingested, decrypted, and parsed securely within localized process loops.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"step-2\",\n      title: \"2. Guardrail Interception Gate\",\n      status: \"verified\",\n      metric: \"Active (99.8% pass)\",\n      desc: \"Model guardrails perform context analysis, PII redact screening, and validation checks against active ISO-27001 rulesets.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"step-3\",\n      title: \"3. Secure Hardware Enclave\",\n      status: \"verified\",\n      metric: \"AMD SEV-SNP Locked\",\n      desc: \"Execution of inference occurs in physically isolated hardware security enclaves with independent memory partition locks.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"step-4\",\n      title: \"4. Human Oversight Interlock\",\n      status: \"warning\",\n      metric: `${pendingOversights} Handshakes Pending`,\n      desc: \"Sensitive boundary adjustments or clearance elevations are paused at the hardware layer, awaiting client admin signatures.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"step-5\",\n      title: \"5. Sealed State Ledger\",\n      status: \"verified\",\n      metric: \"SHA-256 Seal Active\",\n      desc: \"Completed transactions are stamped with immutable cryptographic signatures and committed to the workspace auditing ledger.\"\n    }\n  ];\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6 max-w-[1700px] mx-auto pb-16 select-none animate-slide-up\">\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          A. OFFICIAL COMPLIANCE WORKFLOW DISCLAIMER\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"border border-[#009DFF]/20 bg-[#009DFF]/5 rounded-xl p-4 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between gap-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-relaxed relative overflow-hidden\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-start gap-3 text-white/80 max-w-4xl\">\n          <ShieldAlert className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#009DFF] shrink-0 mt-0.5\" />\n          <span>\n            <strong className=\"text-white\">SOVEREIGN WORKFLOW NOTICE:</strong> This secure workspace is <strong className=\"text-[#009DFF]\">designed to support governance workflows</strong>.\n            All checks, policy configurations, and cryptographic ledger stamps are automated sandbox bounds simulated to assist your risk management audits. GFF AI provides deep-layer infrastructure telemetry, but does not provide legal, formal regulatory, or compliance guarantees.\n          </span>\n        </div>\n        <span className=\"text-[9.5px] text-[#009DFF]/90 font-bold bg-[#009DFF]/15 border border-[#009DFF]/30 px-2.5 py-1 rounded uppercase tracking-wider shrink-0 select-none\">\n          AUDIT COMPANION ACTIVE\n        </span>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          B. TITLE HEADER Section\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-between items-start lg:items-center gap-4 border-b border-white/5 pb-5 select-none\">\n        <div>\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n            <h1 className=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white uppercase font-mono\">Sovereign Governance Workspace</h1>\n            <span className=\"inline-flex rounded bg-[#00FFC2]/10 border border-[#00FFC2]/20 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[9px] font-mono font-bold uppercase text-[#00FFC2]\">\n              LOCKED STATE\n            </span>\n          </div>\n          <p className=\"text-[12.5px] text-white/50 font-mono mt-1 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl\">\n            Real-time interface monitoring automated guardrail checks, pending human-in-the-loop signatures, and certified document governance blocks.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"flex gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] text-white/40 bg-white/[0.01] border border-white/5 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg\">\n          <span>Active Epoch:</span>\n          <span className=\"text-white font-bold\">2026.E3</span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          C. BENTO GRID: STATS & INTERACTIVE ARCHITECTURE GRAPHIC\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6\">\n        \n        {/* Left Column: Metric Cards */}\n        <div className=\"flex flex-col gap-4\">\n          \n          {/* Overall Trust Index Tile */}\n          <WorkspaceCard className=\"flex flex-col justify-between h-[105px] border-[#00FFC2]/10\">\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start\">\n              <span className=\"text-[10.5px] font-mono tracking-wider text-white/40 uppercase block\">Dynamic Trust Index</span>\n              <StatusBadge state=\"active\" label=\"continuous lock\" />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"flex items-end justify-between mt-2\">\n              <div className=\"text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white font-mono\">{dynamicTrustScore}%</div>\n              <div className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-emerald-400 flex items-center gap-1\">\n                <span>Optimized</span>\n                <span className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400 animate-pulse\" />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </WorkspaceCard>\n\n          {/* Active Policies & Checks Tile */}\n          <WorkspaceCard className=\"flex flex-col justify-between h-[105px]\">\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start\">\n              <span className=\"text-[10.5px] font-mono tracking-wider text-white/40 uppercase block\">Active Policies & AI Checks</span>\n              <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-[#009DFF]/20\">AUTOMATED</span>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"flex items-end justify-between mt-2\">\n              <div className=\"text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white font-mono\">{totalPolicies}</div>\n              <div className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50\">\n                {compliantPolicies} Compliant • {warningPolicies} Alerts\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </WorkspaceCard>\n\n          {/* Pending Oversight Interlocks Tile */}\n          <WorkspaceCard className={`flex flex-col justify-between h-[105px] transition-all ${\n            pendingOversights > 0 ? \"border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/[0.01]\" : \"\"\n          }`}>\n            <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start\">\n              <span className=\"text-[10.5px] font-mono tracking-wider text-white/40 uppercase block\">Pending Human Interlocks</span>\n              {pendingOversights > 0 ? (\n                <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-amber-400 bg-amber-400/10 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-amber-400/20 animate-pulse\">ACTION REQ</span>\n              ) : (\n                <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/30\">CLEAR</span>\n              )}\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"flex items-end justify-between mt-2\">\n              <div className=\"text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white font-mono\">{pendingOversights}</div>\n              <div className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/50\">\n                Awaiting manual credential key signature\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </WorkspaceCard>\n\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Right Column: Dynamic SVG / CSS Flowchart (Spans 2 columns on large displays) */}\n        <div className=\"lg:col-span-2 flex flex-col\">\n          <div className=\"p-5 rounded-2xl border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-sm relative overflow-hidden flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-5 items-stretch h-full\">\n            \n            {/* Inline CSS Keyframe for the Flow Line */}\n            <style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: `\n              @keyframes flow {\n                to {\n                  stroke-dashoffset: -20;\n                }\n              }\n              .animate-flow-line {\n                stroke-dasharray: 6, 4;\n                animation: flow 1s linear infinite;\n              }\n            `}} />\n\n            {/* Left Box inside Diagram: 5 interactive sequential nodes */}\n            <div className=\"flex-grow flex flex-col justify-between gap-4\">\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-2\">\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n                  <Layers className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#009DFF]\" />\n                  <span className=\"font-mono text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider\">Enclave Interceptor & Guardrail Topology</span>\n                </div>\n                <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase\">Click node to inspect</span>\n              </div>\n              \n              <div className=\"grid grid-cols-5 gap-2 relative py-4 select-none\">\n                {/* SVG Connecting Flow Lines underneath nodes */}\n                <div className=\"absolute top-[35px] left-[10%] right-[10%] h-[2px] z-0 hidden sm:block\">\n                  <svg className=\"w-full h-[2px] overflow-visible\">\n                    <line \n                      x1=\"0\" y1=\"1\" x2=\"100%\" y2=\"1\" \n                      stroke=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.05)\" \n                      strokeWidth=\"2\" \n                    />\n                    <line \n                      x1=\"0\" y1=\"1\" x2=\"100%\" y2=\"1\" \n                      stroke=\"#00FFC2\" \n                      strokeWidth=\"1.5\" \n                      className=\"animate-flow-line opacity-30\" \n                    />\n                  </svg>\n                </div>\n                \n                {diagramSteps.map((step, idx) => {\n                  const isActive = activeStep === step.id;\n                  \n                  // Custom theme parameters for different steps in topology\n                  const colorClass = \n                    step.id === \"step-1\" ? \"border-sky-500/10 hover:border-sky-500/30 text-sky-400\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-2\" ? \"border-cyan-500/10 hover:border-cyan-500/30 text-cyan-400\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-3\" ? \"border-violet-500/10 hover:border-violet-500/30 text-violet-400\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-4\" ? \"border-amber-500/10 hover:border-amber-500/30 text-amber-400\" :\n                    \"border-emerald-500/10 hover:border-emerald-500/30 text-emerald-400\";\n                  \n                  const bgGlow = \n                    step.id === \"step-1\" && isActive ? \"shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(14,165,233,0.1)] border-sky-500/40 bg-sky-950/15\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-2\" && isActive ? \"shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(6,182,212,0.1)] border-cyan-500/40 bg-cyan-950/15\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-3\" && isActive ? \"shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(139,92,246,0.1)] border-violet-500/40 bg-violet-950/15\" :\n                    step.id === \"step-4\" && isActive ? \"shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(245,158,11,0.1)] border-amber-500/40 bg-amber-950/15\" :\n                    isActive ? \"shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(16,185,129,0.1)] border-emerald-500/40 bg-emerald-950/15\" : \"bg-black/45\";\n                  \n                  return (\n                    <button \n                      key={step.id}\n                      onClick={() => setActiveStep(step.id)}\n                      className={`z-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-xl border transition-all cursor-pointer ${colorClass} ${bgGlow}`}\n                    >\n                      <div className={`w-9 h-9 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center border transition-all ${\n                        isActive ? \"border-current bg-white/[0.03] scale-105\" : \"border-white/10\"\n                      }`}>\n                        {step.id === \"step-1\" && <Cpu className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                        {step.id === \"step-2\" && <ShieldCheck className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                        {step.id === \"step-3\" && <Lock className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                        {step.id === \"step-4\" && <UserCheck className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                        {step.id === \"step-5\" && <FileText className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                      </div>\n                      \n                      <div className=\"text-center font-mono select-none\">\n                        <span className=\"block text-[8px] uppercase tracking-wide text-white/30\">Node 0{idx+1}</span>\n                        <span className={`hidden sm:inline-block font-bold text-[9px] mt-0.5 truncate max-w-[70px] text-white/80`}>\n                          {step.id === \"step-1\" ? \"Ingress\" :\n                           step.id === \"step-2\" ? \"Guardrail\" :\n                           step.id === \"step-3\" ? \"Enclave\" :\n                           step.id === \"step-4\" ? \"Oversight\" : \"Ledger\"}\n                        </span>\n                      </div>\n                    </button>\n                  );\n                })}\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            {/* Right Box: Selected node detail terminal */}\n            <div className=\"w-full md:w-[250px] shrink-0 p-4 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/70 flex flex-col justify-between font-mono text-xs select-text\">\n              {(() => {\n                const activeInfo = diagramSteps.find(s => s.id === activeStep) || diagramSteps[0];\n                return (\n                  <div className=\"space-y-3 h-full flex flex-col justify-between\">\n                    <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n                      <span className=\"text-[8.5px] uppercase text-[#009DFF] font-bold tracking-wider\">REAL-TIME TELEMETRY</span>\n                      <p className=\"text-white font-bold text-[12px]\">{activeInfo.title}</p>\n                      \n                      <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 py-1 px-2 rounded bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 text-[9.5px]\">\n                        <span className={`w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full ${activeInfo.status === \"verified\" ? \"bg-green-400\" : \"bg-amber-400\"}`} />\n                        <span className=\"text-white/45\">State:</span>\n                        <span className={activeInfo.status === \"verified\" ? \"text-green-400 font-bold\" : \"text-amber-400 font-bold\"}>\n                          {activeInfo.metric}\n                        </span>\n                      </div>\n                      \n                      <p className=\"text-[10.5px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed pt-1 select-text\">\n                        {activeInfo.desc}\n                      </p>\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <div className=\"text-[8.5px] text-white/30 border-t border-white/5 pt-2 flex items-center gap-1\">\n                      <Lock className=\"w-3 h-3 text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                      <span>Mathematical boundary locked</span>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                );\n              })()}\n            </div>\n\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n      </div>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          D. INTERACTIVE FILTERS BLOCK\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"p-4 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#070707]/60 backdrop-blur-sm space-y-3 select-none\">\n        <div className=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between gap-2 border-b border-white/5 pb-2\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n            <SlidersHorizontal className=\"w-4 h-4 text-white/50\" />\n            <h3 className=\"font-mono text-xs font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider\">Governance Filters</h3>\n          </div>\n          {(selectedProject || selectedAgent || selectedStatus || selectedSeverity || searchTerm) && (\n            <button \n              onClick={handleResetFilters}\n              className=\"flex items-center gap-1 font-mono text-[10px] text-amber-500 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors cursor-pointer\"\n            >\n              <RotateCcw className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n              <span>Reset Active Filters</span>\n            </button>\n          )}\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-3\">\n          \n          {/* Project Filter */}\n          <div className=\"relative\">\n            <label className=\"block text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mb-1\">Audit Project Target</label>\n            <select \n              value={selectedProject}\n              onChange={(e) => {\n                setSelectedProject(e.target.value);\n                addToast(\"Filtered target project updated\", \"info\");\n              }}\n              className=\"w-full h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.02] px-3 pr-8 text-[11px] font-mono text-white/80 focus:text-white focus:border-white/15 outline-none transition-all cursor-pointer appearance-none\"\n            >\n              <option value=\"\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white/50\">ALL PROJECTS</option>\n              {projectOptions.map(p => (\n                <option key={p.id} value={p.id} className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white\">\n                  {p.name.toUpperCase()}\n                </option>\n              ))}\n            </select>\n            <ChevronDown className=\"absolute right-3 top-6.5 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30 pointer-events-none\" />\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Agent Filter */}\n          <div className=\"relative\">\n            <label className=\"block text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mb-1\">Sovereign Agent Enclave</label>\n            <select \n              value={selectedAgent}\n              onChange={(e) => {\n                setSelectedAgent(e.target.value);\n                addToast(\"Filtered agent target updated\", \"info\");\n              }}\n              className=\"w-full h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.02] px-3 pr-8 text-[11px] font-mono text-white/80 focus:text-white focus:border-white/15 outline-none transition-all cursor-pointer appearance-none\"\n            >\n              <option value=\"\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white/50\">ALL AGENTS</option>\n              {agentOptions.map(a => (\n                <option key={a.id} value={a.id} className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white\">\n                  {a.name}\n                </option>\n              ))}\n            </select>\n            <ChevronDown className=\"absolute right-3 top-6.5 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30 pointer-events-none\" />\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Status Filter */}\n          <div className=\"relative\">\n            <label className=\"block text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mb-1\">Compliance State</label>\n            <select \n              value={selectedStatus}\n              onChange={(e) => {\n                setSelectedStatus(e.target.value);\n                addToast(`State filter locked to ${e.target.value || \"all\"}`, \"info\");\n              }}\n              className=\"w-full h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.02] px-3 pr-8 text-[11px] font-mono text-white/80 focus:text-white focus:border-white/15 outline-none transition-all cursor-pointer appearance-none\"\n            >\n              <option value=\"\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white/50\">ALL COMPLIANCE STATES</option>\n              <option value=\"compliant\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-green-400\">COMPLIANT</option>\n              <option value=\"warning\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-amber-400\">WARNING ALERT</option>\n              <option value=\"critical\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-red-500\">CRITICAL FAULT</option>\n            </select>\n            <ChevronDown className=\"absolute right-3 top-6.5 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30 pointer-events-none\" />\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Severity Filter */}\n          <div className=\"relative\">\n            <label className=\"block text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mb-1\">Policy Risk Severity</label>\n            <select \n              value={selectedSeverity}\n              onChange={(e) => {\n                setSelectedSeverity(e.target.value);\n                addToast(`Risk filter locked to ${e.target.value || \"all\"}`, \"info\");\n              }}\n              className=\"w-full h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.02] px-3 pr-8 text-[11px] font-mono text-white/80 focus:text-white focus:border-white/15 outline-none transition-all cursor-pointer appearance-none\"\n            >\n              <option value=\"\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-white/50\">ALL RISK SEVERITIES</option>\n              <option value=\"high\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-red-400 font-bold\">HIGH RISK</option>\n              <option value=\"medium\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-amber-400\">MEDIUM RISK</option>\n              <option value=\"low\" className=\"bg-[#0c0c0c] text-blue-400\">LOW RISK</option>\n            </select>\n            <ChevronDown className=\"absolute right-3 top-6.5 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30 pointer-events-none\" />\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Free Text Search Filter */}\n          <div className=\"relative\">\n            <label className=\"block text-[8.5px] font-mono text-white/40 uppercase mb-1\">Search Audit Logs / Rules</label>\n            <div className=\"relative\">\n              <Search className=\"absolute left-2.5 top-2.5 w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30\" />\n              <input \n                type=\"text\"\n                value={searchTerm}\n                onChange={(e) => setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}\n                placeholder=\"Search ISO-27001, keys, rules...\"\n                className=\"w-full h-9 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-white/[0.02] pl-8 pr-7 text-[11px] font-mono text-white placeholder-white/30 focus:border-white/15 outline-none transition-all\"\n              />\n              {searchTerm && (\n                <button \n                  onClick={() => setSearchTerm(\"\")}\n                  className=\"absolute right-2 top-2.5 hover:text-white text-white/30\"\n                >\n                  <X className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n                </button>\n              )}\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          E. DYNAMIC TABS HUB & MAIN TABLES/LISTS\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n        \n        {/* Tab Headers */}\n        <div className=\"flex border-b border-white/5 gap-6 select-none font-mono\">\n          \n          <button \n            onClick={() => setActiveTab(\"policies\")}\n            className={`py-3 text-[12px] font-bold uppercase transition-all relative flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer ${\n              activeTab === \"policies\" ? \"text-white\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/70\"\n            }`}\n          >\n            <span>AI Checks & Policies</span>\n            <span className={`px-1 rounded text-[9.5px] ${\n              activeTab === \"policies\" ? \"bg-white/10 text-white\" : \"bg-white/5 text-white/30\"\n            }`}>\n              {filteredPolicies.length}\n            </span>\n            {activeTab === \"policies\" && (\n              <span className=\"absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-[1.5px] bg-[#00FFC2]\" />\n            )}\n          </button>\n\n          <button \n            onClick={() => setActiveTab(\"oversight\")}\n            className={`py-3 text-[12px] font-bold uppercase transition-all relative flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer ${\n              activeTab === \"oversight\" ? \"text-white\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/70\"\n            }`}\n          >\n            <span>Human Oversight Interlocks</span>\n            <span className={`px-1 rounded text-[9.5px] ${\n              activeTab === \"oversight\" ? \"bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-500\" : \"bg-white/5 text-white/30\"\n            }`}>\n              {filteredApprovals.length}\n            </span>\n            {activeTab === \"oversight\" && (\n              <span className=\"absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-[1.5px] bg-[#00FFC2]\" />\n            )}\n          </button>\n\n          <button \n            onClick={() => setActiveTab(\"documents\")}\n            className={`py-3 text-[12px] font-bold uppercase transition-all relative flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer ${\n              activeTab === \"documents\" ? \"text-white\" : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/70\"\n            }`}\n          >\n            <span>Document Governance Ledger</span>\n            <span className={`px-1 rounded text-[9.5px] ${\n              activeTab === \"documents\" ? \"bg-white/10 text-white\" : \"bg-white/5 text-white/30\"\n            }`}>\n              {filteredDocuments.length}\n            </span>\n            {activeTab === \"documents\" && (\n              <span className=\"absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-[1.5px] bg-[#00FFC2]\" />\n            )}\n          </button>\n\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Tab Interior Content Panels */}\n        <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n          \n          {/* TAB 1: AI CHECKS & POLICIES LIST */}\n          {activeTab === \"policies\" && (\n            <div className=\"space-y-3\">\n              {filteredPolicies.length === 0 ? (\n                <div className=\"p-12 border border-dashed border-white/5 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.01] text-center font-mono max-w-xl mx-auto space-y-4\">\n                  <ShieldAlert className=\"w-8 h-8 text-white/20 mx-auto\" />\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                    <p className=\"text-white font-bold text-xs\">NO CONFORME POLICIES DETECTED</p>\n                    <p className=\"text-white/40 text-[11px] leading-relaxed\">\n                      No active AI guardrail policies match your current selection parameters. Try resetting your filters.\n                    </p>\n                  </div>\n                  <button \n                    onClick={handleResetFilters}\n                    className=\"h-8 px-3 rounded border border-white/15 hover:border-white/25 text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-white transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n                  >\n                    Clear All Filters\n                  </button>\n                </div>\n              ) : (\n                filteredPolicies.map((policy) => {\n                  const isExpanded = expandedPolicyId === policy.id;\n                  \n                  return (\n                    <div \n                      key={policy.id}\n                      className={`rounded-xl border transition-all ${\n                        isExpanded ? \"border-white/15 bg-white/[0.02]\" : \"border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/30 hover:border-white/10\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      {/* Accordion Header */}\n                      <div \n                        onClick={() => setExpandedPolicyId(isExpanded ? null : policy.id)}\n                        className=\"p-4 flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer select-none font-mono text-xs\"\n                      >\n                        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3 min-w-0\">\n                          {policy.status === \"compliant\" ? (\n                            <CheckCircle className=\"w-4 h-4 text-[#00FFC2] shrink-0\" />\n                          ) : policy.status === \"warning\" ? (\n                            <AlertCircle className=\"w-4 h-4 text-amber-400 shrink-0\" />\n                          ) : (\n                            <ShieldAlert className=\"w-4 h-4 text-red-500 shrink-0\" />\n                          )}\n                          <div className=\"min-w-0\">\n                            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap\">\n                              <span className=\"font-bold text-white/50 text-[10px] tracking-wider shrink-0\">{policy.id}</span>\n                              <span className=\"text-white font-bold truncate\">{policy.name}</span>\n                              <span className={`text-[9px] px-1 py-0.1 border rounded font-mono shrink-0 ${\n                                policy.severity === \"high\" ? \"text-red-400 border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5\" :\n                                policy.severity === \"medium\" ? \"text-amber-400 border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5\" :\n                                \"text-blue-400 border-blue-500/20 bg-blue-500/5\"\n                              }`}>\n                                {policy.severity.toUpperCase()}\n                              </span>\n                            </div>\n                            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 mt-1 text-[10.5px] text-white/40 flex-wrap\">\n                              <span>Standard: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{policy.standard}</strong></span>\n                              <span>•</span>\n                              <span>Project: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{policy.projectName}</strong></span>\n                              <span>•</span>\n                              <span>Agent: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{policy.agentName}</strong></span>\n                            </div>\n                          </div>\n                        </div>\n\n                        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-4 shrink-0\">\n                          <span className={`text-[9.5px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider hidden sm:inline-block ${\n                            policy.status === \"compliant\" ? \"text-[#00FFC2]\" :\n                            policy.status === \"warning\" ? \"text-amber-400\" : \"text-red-500\"\n                          }`}>\n                            {policy.status === \"compliant\" ? \"COMPLIANT LOCK\" :\n                             policy.status === \"warning\" ? \"WARNING THRESHOLD\" : \"CRITICAL ALERT\"}\n                          </span>\n                          {isExpanded ? (\n                            <ChevronDown className=\"w-4 h-4 text-white/40\" />\n                          ) : (\n                            <ChevronRight className=\"w-4 h-4 text-white/40\" />\n                          )}\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n\n                      {/* Accordion Expand Body */}\n                      {isExpanded && (\n                        <div className=\"px-4 pb-4 border-t border-white/5 pt-4 font-mono text-xs text-white/80 space-y-4\">\n                          <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4\">\n                            \n                            {/* Enforcement Description */}\n                            <div className=\"md:col-span-2 p-3.5 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/50 space-y-1.5\">\n                              <span className=\"text-[9px] text-[#009DFF] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider block\">Boundary Enforcement Specification</span>\n                              <p className=\"text-[11.5px] leading-relaxed text-white/70 select-text\">\n                                {policy.desc}\n                              </p>\n                              <div className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 pt-1\">\n                                Last Continuous Verification Hash Check: <span className=\"text-white/60\">0xSHA2026_99F_02</span>\n                              </div>\n                            </div>\n\n                            {/* Verification Stats metadata */}\n                            <div className=\"p-3.5 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202]/50 space-y-2 flex flex-col justify-between\">\n                              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                                <span className=\"text-[9px] text-[#009DFF] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider block\">Audit Ledger Identity</span>\n                                <div className=\"text-[10.5px] space-y-1 text-white/60\">\n                                  <div className=\"flex justify-between\"><span>Rule Type:</span> <span className=\"text-white font-bold\">{policy.standard}</span></div>\n                                  <div className=\"flex justify-between\"><span>Last Checked:</span> <span className=\"text-white\">{new Date(policy.lastChecked).toLocaleString()}</span></div>\n                                  <div className=\"flex justify-between\"><span>Audit Scope:</span> <span className=\"text-white\">Continuous</span></div>\n                                </div>\n                              </div>\n                              \n                              <button \n                                onClick={() => handleVerifyPolicy(policy.id)}\n                                disabled={verifyingId !== null}\n                                className=\"w-full h-8 rounded bg-white/5 hover:bg-white/10 text-[10.5px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:opacity-50\"\n                              >\n                                {verifyingId === policy.id ? (\n                                  <>\n                                    <RefreshCw className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 animate-spin text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                                    <span>Verifying Handshake...</span>\n                                  </>\n                                ) : (\n                                  <>\n                                    <ShieldCheck className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                                    <span>Manually Re-verify Boundary</span>\n                                  </>\n                                )}\n                              </button>\n                            </div>\n\n                          </div>\n\n                          {/* Technical Logs console */}\n                          <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n                            <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-1\">\n                              <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1 text-[9px] text-white/40 font-bold uppercase\">\n                                <Cpu className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#009DFF]\" />\n                                <span>SECURE COMPLIANCE Telemetry FLUX Logs</span>\n                              </div>\n                              <span className=\"text-[8px] text-white/30\">100% Deterministic Demo Ledger</span>\n                            </div>\n                            <div className=\"p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/5 bg-[#020202] text-[10.5px] font-mono text-white/70 space-y-1.5 max-h-[140px] overflow-y-auto select-text\">\n                              {policy.logs.map((log, idx) => (\n                                <div key={idx} className=\"leading-relaxed border-b border-white/[0.02] pb-0.5 last:border-0 font-mono\">\n                                  <span className=\"text-[#009DFF]/70 mr-1\">&gt;</span> {log}\n                                </div>\n                              ))}\n                              <div className=\"text-[9.5px] text-white/30 pt-1 flex items-center gap-1 select-none\">\n                                <Lock className=\"w-3 h-3 text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                                <span>State cryptographic handshakes sealed in AMD SEV enclave memory partition</span>\n                              </div>\n                            </div>\n                          </div>\n\n                        </div>\n                      )}\n                    </div>\n                  );\n                })\n              )}\n            </div>\n          )}\n\n          {/* TAB 2: HUMAN OVERSIGHT POINTS */}\n          {activeTab === \"oversight\" && (\n            <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n              {filteredApprovals.length === 0 ? (\n                <div className=\"p-12 border border-dashed border-white/5 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.01] text-center font-mono max-w-xl mx-auto space-y-4\">\n                  <UserCheck className=\"w-8 h-8 text-white/20 mx-auto\" />\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                    <p className=\"text-white font-bold text-xs\">NO INTERLOCKS REQUIRING ATTENTION</p>\n                    <p className=\"text-white/40 text-[11px] leading-relaxed\">\n                      All human oversight points and cryptographic enclave adjustments are signed off and active.\n                    </p>\n                  </div>\n                  <button \n                    onClick={handleResetFilters}\n                    className=\"h-8 px-3 rounded border border-white/15 hover:border-white/25 text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-white transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n                  >\n                    Clear All Filters\n                  </button>\n                </div>\n              ) : (\n                <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n                  {filteredApprovals.map((item) => (\n                    <div \n                      key={item.id}\n                      className={`rounded-xl border p-5 font-mono text-xs flex flex-col justify-between gap-4 transition-all bg-[#050505]/40 ${\n                        item.status === \"pending\"\n                          ? \"border-amber-500/25 bg-amber-500/[0.01]\"\n                          : item.status === \"approved\"\n                          ? \"border-emerald-500/10\"\n                          : \"border-red-500/10 opacity-60\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      <div className=\"space-y-3\">\n                        {/* Title and ID */}\n                        <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start gap-2\">\n                          <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                            <span className=\"text-[9px] text-[#009DFF] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider block\">\n                              {item.category.toUpperCase()} • {item.id}\n                            </span>\n                            <h4 className=\"text-[13px] font-bold text-white leading-normal select-text\">{item.title}</h4>\n                          </div>\n                          \n                          <span className={`text-[9px] font-bold font-mono px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border ${\n                            item.status === \"pending\" ? \"text-amber-400 border-amber-400/20 bg-amber-400/5 animate-pulse\" :\n                            item.status === \"approved\" ? \"text-green-400 border-green-500/20 bg-green-500/5\" :\n                            \"text-red-400 border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5\"\n                          }`}>\n                            {item.status.toUpperCase()}\n                          </span>\n                        </div>\n\n                        {/* Associations */}\n                        <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-[10.5px] border-y border-white/5 py-2.5 text-white/50\">\n                          <div>\n                            Target Project: <strong className=\"text-white/70 block truncate\">{item.project}</strong>\n                          </div>\n                          <div>\n                            Target Enclave Agent: <strong className=\"text-white/70 block truncate\">{item.agent}</strong>\n                          </div>\n                          <div className=\"mt-1\">\n                            Requester Identity: <strong className=\"text-white/70 block truncate\">{item.requester}</strong>\n                          </div>\n                          <div className=\"mt-1\">\n                            Requested Time: <strong className=\"text-white/70 block truncate\">{new Date(item.requestDate).toLocaleString()}</strong>\n                          </div>\n                        </div>\n\n                        {/* Context Request details */}\n                        <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                          <span className=\"text-[8.5px] text-white/35 uppercase font-bold tracking-wider\">Adjustment Parameters Spec</span>\n                          <p className=\"text-[11px] leading-relaxed text-white/60 bg-black/40 p-3 rounded-lg border border-white/5 select-text\">\n                            {item.desc}\n                          </p>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n\n                      {/* Pending Interactive Decision Actions */}\n                      {item.status === \"pending\" ? (\n                        <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 pt-2 select-none\">\n                          <button \n                            onClick={() => handleResolveApproval(item.id, \"rejected\")}\n                            className=\"h-8.5 rounded border border-red-500/20 hover:border-red-500/30 hover:bg-red-500/5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-red-400 transition-all flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 cursor-pointer\"\n                          >\n                            <ThumbsDown className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n                            <span>Decline Signature</span>\n                          </button>\n                          <button \n                            onClick={() => handleResolveApproval(item.id, \"approved\")}\n                            className=\"h-8.5 rounded bg-[#00FFC2] hover:bg-[#00e0aa] text-[#020202] text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(0,255,194,0.1)]\"\n                          >\n                            <ThumbsUp className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n                            <span>Approve & Sign Seal</span>\n                          </button>\n                        </div>\n                      ) : (\n                        <div className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 border-t border-white/5 pt-3 flex items-center gap-1.5 select-none\">\n                          <UserCheck className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white/30\" />\n                          <span>\n                            Decision committed by client user alex.mercer. Signed with HSM security seal.\n                          </span>\n                        </div>\n                      )}\n                    </div>\n                  ))}\n                </div>\n              )}\n            </div>\n          )}\n\n          {/* TAB 3: DOCUMENT GOVERNANCE HUB */}\n          {activeTab === \"documents\" && (\n            <div className=\"space-y-3\">\n              {filteredDocuments.length === 0 ? (\n                <div className=\"p-12 border border-dashed border-white/5 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.01] text-center font-mono max-w-xl mx-auto space-y-4\">\n                  <FileText className=\"w-8 h-8 text-white/20 mx-auto\" />\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                    <p className=\"text-white font-bold text-xs\">NO LEDGER CERTIFICATES FOUND</p>\n                    <p className=\"text-white/40 text-[11px] leading-relaxed\">\n                      No certified governance files or compliance documents match your selection parameters.\n                    </p>\n                  </div>\n                  <button \n                    onClick={handleResetFilters}\n                    className=\"h-8 px-3 rounded border border-white/15 hover:border-white/25 text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-white transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n                  >\n                    Clear All Filters\n                  </button>\n                </div>\n              ) : (\n                filteredDocuments.map((doc) => (\n                  <div \n                    key={doc.id}\n                    className=\"p-4 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/30 hover:border-white/10 transition-all font-mono text-xs flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between gap-4\"\n                  >\n                    <div className=\"flex items-start gap-3 min-w-0\">\n                      <div className=\"w-9 h-9 rounded bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0\">\n                        <FileText className=\"w-4 h-4 text-white/60\" />\n                      </div>\n                      \n                      <div className=\"min-w-0\">\n                        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap\">\n                          <span className=\"font-bold text-white text-[12.5px] select-text truncate\">{doc.name}</span>\n                          <span className=\"text-[9.5px] px-1.5 py-0.2 rounded bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-white/50\">\n                            {doc.format}\n                          </span>\n                          <span className=\"text-[8.5px] px-1.5 py-0.2 rounded bg-[#009DFF]/10 border border-[#009DFF]/20 text-[#009DFF]\">\n                            {doc.clearanceLevel}\n                          </span>\n                        </div>\n                        \n                        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 mt-1 text-[10px] text-white/40 flex-wrap\">\n                          <span>Size: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{doc.size}</strong></span>\n                          <span>•</span>\n                          <span>Audit Type: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{doc.category.toUpperCase()}</strong></span>\n                          <span>•</span>\n                          <span>Target Project: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{doc.projectName}</strong></span>\n                          <span>•</span>\n                          <span>Agent: <strong className=\"text-white/60\">{doc.agentName}</strong></span>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    {/* Cryptographic Seal Actions */}\n                    <div className=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 shrink-0\">\n                      \n                      {/* Copyable cryptographic seal hash button */}\n                      <button \n                        onClick={() => handleCopyHash(doc.hash)}\n                        className=\"h-8 rounded border border-white/5 bg-[#020202] px-2.5 text-[10px] text-white/50 hover:text-white hover:border-white/10 transition-colors flex items-center gap-1.5 max-w-[180px] cursor-pointer\"\n                        title=\"Copy Cryptographic Hash Seal\"\n                      >\n                        <Lock className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                        <span className=\"truncate font-mono text-[9px] select-all\">{doc.hash.substring(0, 10)}...{doc.hash.slice(-6)}</span>\n                        <Copy className=\"w-3 h-3 text-white/30 shrink-0\" />\n                      </button>\n\n                      {/* Compile export button */}\n                      <button \n                        onClick={() => handleExportDocument(doc.id)}\n                        disabled={exportingId !== null}\n                        className=\"h-8 px-3 rounded bg-white/5 hover:bg-white/10 text-[10.5px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 transition-all cursor-pointer disabled:opacity-50\"\n                      >\n                        {exportingId === doc.id ? (\n                          <>\n                            <RefreshCw className=\"w-3 h-3 animate-spin text-[#00FFC2]\" />\n                            <span>Compiling Export...</span>\n                          </>\n                        ) : (\n                          <>\n                            <Download className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n                            <span>Request Certified Export</span>\n                          </>\n                        )}\n                      </button>\n\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                ))\n              )}\n            </div>\n          )}\n\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          F. PREMIUM ENTERPRISE CONTACT CALL-TO-ACTION\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <WorkspaceCard className=\"mt-8 border-[#009DFF]/10 bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-[#009DFF]/[0.01] to-transparent p-6 text-center select-none font-mono\">\n        <div className=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-4\">\n          <ShieldCheck className=\"w-7 h-7 text-[#00FFC2] mx-auto animate-pulse-glow\" />\n          <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n            <h3 className=\"text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wider\">Expand Governance Boundaries</h3>\n            <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50 leading-relaxed\">\n              Require bespoke hardware enclaves, customized audit rulesets, or physical HSM integration?\n              GFF AI Sovereign systems are designed to support customized, enterprise-grade governance and risk workflows.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"pt-2\">\n            <a \n              href=\"/portal/support\"\n              className=\"inline-flex h-9 items-center gap-1.5 px-4 rounded bg-white/5 hover:bg-white/10 text-[10.5px] font-bold uppercase text-white border border-white/10 transition-all cursor-pointer\"\n            >\n              <span>Initialize Architect Consultation</span>\n              <ExternalLink className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </WorkspaceCard>\n\n      {/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n          G. INLINE TOAST SYSTEM\n          ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */}\n      <div className=\"fixed bottom-6 right-6 z-50 flex flex-col gap-2 pointer-events-none select-none\">\n        {toasts.map(toast => (\n          <div \n            key={toast.id}\n            className={`p-3.5 rounded-xl shadow-2xl border text-[11px] font-mono font-bold flex items-center gap-3 animate-slide-up pointer-events-auto max-w-sm ${\n              toast.type === \"success\" \n                ? \"bg-[#020202]/95 border-[#00FFC2]/30 text-[#00FFC2] shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(0,255,194,0.15)]\" \n                : toast.type === \"warning\"\n                ? \"bg-[#020202]/95 border-amber-500/30 text-amber-500 shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(245,158,11,0.15)]\"\n                : \"bg-[#020202]/95 border-[#009DFF]/30 text-[#009DFF] shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(0,157,255,0.15)]\"\n            }`}\n          >\n            {toast.type === \"success\" && <CheckCircle className=\"w-4 h-4 text-[#00FFC2] shrink-0\" />}\n            {toast.type === \"warning\" && <AlertCircle className=\"w-4 h-4 text-amber-500 shrink-0\" />}\n            {toast.type === \"info\" && <Info className=\"w-4 h-4 text-[#009DFF] shrink-0\" />}\n            <span className=\"leading-tight\">{toast.message}</span>\n          </div>\n        ))}\n      </div>\n\n      {/* Helper animations definition */}\n      <style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: `\n        @keyframes slideUp {\n          from {\n            opacity: 0;\n            transform: translateY(12px);\n          }\n          to {\n            opacity: 1;\n            transform: translateY(0);\n          }\n        }\n        .animate-slide-up {\n          animation: slideUp 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) forwards;\n        }\n        \n        @keyframes pulseGlow {\n          0%, 100% {\n            filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(0, 255, 194, 0.2));\n          }\n          50% {\n            filter: drop-shadow(0 0 12px rgba(0, 255, 194, 0.5));\n          }\n        }\n        .animate-pulse-glow {\n          animation: pulseGlow 2.5s infinite ease-in-out;\n        }\n      `}} />\n\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
